title: For Sale:  Pinkerton Detective Agency Employee Owned Cased Remington Smoot Revolver (AH4667)
postcontent: Pinkerton Detective Agency Employee Owned Cased Remington Smoot Revolver. Very fine historical gun. Owned by Pinkerton Detective Agency employee George Bangs. Mr. Bangs was Allan Pinkerton’s right hand man. He was one of the first employees to the agency and became the General Superintendent of the Pinkerton Detective Agency. This meant he was the man in charge who ran the business. The Pinkerton Detective Agency while a private company, was almost an unofficial Government Agency that acted as The Secret Service, FBI. The agency did everything from thwarting attempts on President Lincoln’s life to breaking up Union riots to having the shootout with the “Wild Bunch” to pursuing Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid and much more in between. The Pinkerton Detective Agency was the very first private detective firm. Pinkerton became known to criminals as “The Eye” which led to the term “Private Eye” and then became Private Investigator. A picture of an eye and the words “We Never Sleep” was the logo of The Pinkerton Detective Agency. This revolver is a first model Remington Smoot revolver. The gun is in new condition with nickel finish and a gold plated cylinder. This gun has beautiful pearl grips that have an escutcheon on the left hand side that has the name “George Bangs”. The case has a silver escutcheon in a banner on the lid with the eye and the agency motto of “We Never Sleep”. This is a fantastic historical set! Along with this gun comes a binder of research into Mr. Bangs along with pictures and correspondence between the previous collector and The Pinkerton Detective Agency.http://www.collectorsfirearms.com/pinkerton-detective-agency-employee-owned-cased-remington-smoot-revolver-ah4667/

title: For Sale:  Lee Enfield #4 MK1 - Lend Lease Rifle (Made by Savage in USA)
postcontent: For sale is a Lee Enfield No 4 Mk 1 rifle. These rifles were normally manufactured in Britain, but at the start of World War 2, the British contracted the USA through the Lend-Lease program to build rifles and other equipment. This is one of those rifles. It's marked "U.S. Property" - see pictures. The British did this because they didn't have the means of production to go toe-to-toe with NAZI Germany. These rifles were made from 1941 to 1944 - Legit WW2 production rifle. The rifle shoots .303 British. Has very good bore with deep rifling. Rifle is very nice looking and in good condition. Comes with sling and bayonet.Non-sporterized, good condition Lee Enfields are getting harder and harder to find, especially legit WW2 rifles like this one. Lee Enfields are arguably one of the best and most accurate rifles of World War 2, definitely a must for any collector. Asking $550 OBO, no trades, shoot me a text or give me a call REDACTED. I can send more pics if needed.
